	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I think it is maybe a little off/incomplete that their twitter is in swedish only, given that in the english language sphere, everyone and their dog seems to be actively tweeting (not least indie game devs) while over here, it's more just the official politicians, journalists, bloggers and lifestyle stars from tv doing it for a more or less half-passive audience. Sure, they keep a lot of their audience updated that way, but if they want to reach out further, i think it'd make sense to at least keep an international counterpart, since they claim (maybe rightly so) to be scandinavias' largest retro games expo. That in itself ought to attract people from all locales with good communications if they had a chance at knowing enough details about it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
